    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:1.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—",
          "en": "So I have heard. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:1.2",
          "pli": "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ",
          "en": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:1.3",
          "pli": "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: ",
          "en": "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:1.4",
          "pli": "“bhikkhavo”ti. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants!” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:1.5",
          "pli": "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. ",
          "en": "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:1.6",
          "pli": "Bhagavā etadavoca: ",
          "en": "The Buddha said this: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:1.7",
          "pli": "“paṭiccasamuppādaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, I will teach you dependent origination. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:1.8",
          "pli": "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti. ",
          "en": "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:1.9",
          "pli": "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. ",
          "en": "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:1.10",
          "pli": "Bhagavā etadavoca: ",
          "en": "The Buddha said this: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:2.1",
          "pli": "“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, paṭiccasamuppādo? ",
          "en": "“And what is dependent origination? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:2.2",
          "pli": "Avijjāpaccayā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā; ",
          "en": "Ignorance is a condition for choices. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:2.3",
          "pli": "saṅkhārapaccayā viññāṇaṃ; ",
          "en": "Choices are a condition for consciousness. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:2.4",
          "pli": "viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpaṃ; ",
          "en": "Consciousness is a condition for name and form. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:2.5",
          "pli": "nāmarūpapaccayā saḷāyatanaṃ; ",
          "en": "Name and form are conditions for the six sense fields. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:2.6",
          "pli": "saḷāyatanapaccayā phasso; ",
          "en": "The six sense fields are conditions for contact. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:2.7",
          "pli": "phassapaccayā vedanā; ",
          "en": "Contact is a condition for feeling. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:2.8",
          "pli": "vedanāpaccayā taṇhā; ",
          "en": "Feeling is a condition for craving. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:2.9",
          "pli": "taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ; ",
          "en": "Craving is a condition for grasping. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:2.10",
          "pli": "upādānapaccayā bhavo; ",
          "en": "Grasping is a condition for continued existence. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:2.11",
          "pli": "bhavapaccayā jāti; ",
          "en": "Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:2.12",
          "pli": "jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti. ",
          "en": "Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:2.13",
          "pli": "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti. ",
          "en": "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:2.14",
          "pli": "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, paṭiccasamuppādo. ",
          "en": "This is called dependent origination. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.1",
          "pli": "Avijjāya tveva asesavirāganirodhā saṅkhāranirodho; ",
          "en": "When ignorance fades away and ceases with nothing left over, choices cease. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.2",
          "pli": "saṅkhāranirodhā viññāṇanirodho; ",
          "en": "When choices cease, consciousness ceases. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.3",
          "pli": "viññāṇanirodhā nāmarūpanirodho; ",
          "en": "When consciousness ceases, name and form cease. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.4",
          "pli": "nāmarūpanirodhā saḷāyatananirodho; ",
          "en": "When name and form cease, the six sense fields cease. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.5",
          "pli": "saḷāyatananirodhā phassanirodho; ",
          "en": "When the six sense fields cease, contact ceases. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.6",
          "pli": "phassanirodhā vedanānirodho; ",
          "en": "When contact ceases, feeling ceases. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.7",
          "pli": "vedanānirodhā taṇhānirodho; ",
          "en": "When feeling ceases, craving ceases. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.8",
          "pli": "taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho; ",
          "en": "When craving ceases, grasping ceases. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.9",
          "pli": "upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho; ",
          "en": "When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.10",
          "pli": "bhavanirodhā jātinirodho; ",
          "en": "When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.11",
          "pli": "jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti. ",
          "en": "When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.12",
          "pli": "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī”ti. ",
          "en": "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.13",
          "pli": "Idamavoca bhagavā. ",
          "en": "That is what the Buddha said. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.14",
          "pli": "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti. ",
          "en": "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.1:3.15",
          "pli": "Paṭhamaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
